  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ignoring the OECD Requirement</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your employer or business must be registered in an OECD member country. If your clients are primarily in non-OECD countries (India, China, Brazil, etc.), you won't qualify. Check OECD membership before investing time in the application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Income Documentation</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You need official verification from your OECD country's tax or social insurance authority—not just bank statements. Plan 1-2 weeks to obtain these documents. Generic employer letters aren't sufficient; you need governmental verification.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Income Below Threshold</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The €2,857-3,843/month threshold is strictly enforced. Income just below the line will likely be rejected. Ensure your documented income clearly exceeds the requirement with buffer room for currency fluctuations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Tax Implications</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">If you stay more than 183 days per year, you become a Latvian tax resident and owe tax on worldwide income (up to 31%). Plan your stay duration or consult a tax advisor if you want to avoid Latvian tax residency.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Working for Latvian Clients</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">DNV holders cannot work for Latvian employers or provide services to Latvian residents. Your income must come entirely from outside Latvia. Taking local work violates your visa conditions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

